      %h4 HIV/AIDS by the numbers:
      %ul
        %li Over 33 million people are living with HIV worldwide; 22.4 are in Sub-Saharan Africa
        %li HIV/AIDS is the leading cause of death worldwide for people ages 15-59
        %li AIDS has orphaned more than 15 million children; today, 1 out of 20 children in Africa is orphaned
        %li Only 1.3 million people who are living with AIDS are receiving treatment
        %li Over 15.7 million women are living with AIDS worldwide; 12 million women are in Sub-Saharan Africa
        %li Each day 1,500 children worldwide become infected with HIV; most are newborn
        %li There are 1.2 million people living with HIV/AIDS in the U.S., including over 6,000 people in King County
  
